Ruck: Once a tackle occurs, players can compete for the ball on the ground by driving over it to push the opposing team back.
Penalty and Free Kicks: Awarded for various infringements. Teams can kick for goal, tap the ball and run, or choose a scrum.
Offside: In general, players are offside if they are in front of a teammate who last played the ball. Players must retreat behind the last foot of the ruck, maul, or scrum to be put inside.
Maul: A maul occurs when the ball carrier is held by one or more opponents, and one or more of the ball carrier's teammates bind on the ball carrier. The ball must not touch the ground.
Lineout: This restarts play after the ball or ball carrier goes into touch. Players from each team line up parallel to each other to compete for the ball thrown in from the sideline.
Knock-On: If the ball is knocked forward with the hand or arm and hits the ground or another player, it results in a scrum to the non-offending team.
Forward Pass: Players cannot pass the ball forward; all passes must go backwards.
Conversion: After a try, the scoring team has the opportunity to kick the ball between the opponent’s goal posts from the ground for an extra two points.

A player loses a point if they fail to hit the ball over the net, if the ball bounces twice on their side, or if they hit the ball out of bounds.
